title: Kenseth still angry with Logano
text:
Kenseth still angry with Logano Still thinks crash was intentional Published On: Oct 23 2015 04:03:20 PM CDT Tweet TALLADEGA, AL - 
Matt Kenseth hasn't softened his stance on last weekend's incident with Joey Logano. He said Logano is "lying" that he didn't wreck Kenseth on purpose. Related Content NFL injury report on Sunday's games By The Sports Xchange 
Kenseth was leading at Kansas Speedway, where a win would have earned him an automatic berth into the third round of NASCAR's playoffs. 
He blocked to prevent Logano from passing him for the lead, but Logano made contact with him that caused Kenseth to spin. 
Kenseth wound up 14th and heads into Sunday's elimination race at Talladega Superspeedway last in the Chase for the Sprint Cup championship field. 
Logano won his second consecutive race and denied intentionally hitting Kenseth. 
Kenseth bristled Friday at Logano's claim and said Logano should stop talking about the incident. He also said the two have not spoken since Kansas.
